### 1. Certificates

#### Data Modeling for Certificates

You would need to create a new Go struct for `Certificate` in the [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/models`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels) directory, similar to how other models like [`Plan`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go#L37) or [`FinancialTransaction`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fbilling.go#L29) are defined (see [Core Data Models and Validation](#core-data-models-and-validation)). This `Certificate` struct would need fields such as:

*   [`ID`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go#L38): [`primitive.ObjectID`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go#L38) for unique identification.
*   `CourseID`: [`primitive.ObjectID`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go#L38) to link to the course it was issued for.
*   [`UserID`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fauth%2Fjwt.go#L23): [`primitive.ObjectID`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go#L38) to link to the learner.
*   [`TenantID`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fstripe%2Fstripe.go#L172): [`primitive.ObjectID`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go#L38) to link to the tenant.
*   `IssueDate`: [`time.Time`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fcmd%2Flastsaas%2Foutput.go#L125) for when the certificate was issued.
*   `VerificationCode`: A unique string for URL verification.
*   `PDFData`: [`[]byte`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fcmd%2Fserver%2Fmain.go#L79) to store the generated PDF content (or a reference to storage if PDFs are stored externally).
*   [`Status`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fhealth.go#L22): e.g., "issued", "revoked".
*   [`CreatedAt`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go#L56), [`UpdatedAt`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go#L57): [`time.Time`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fcmd%2Flastsaas%2Foutput.go#L125) for auditing.

You would also need to add a new collection to [`MongoDB`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fdb%2Fmongodb.go#L15) in [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/db/mongodb.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fdb%2Fmongodb.go) for certificates, and define its JSON schema in [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/db/schema.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fdb%2Fschema.go), similar to [`financialTransactionsSchema`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fdb%2Fschema.go#L304) or [`customPagesSchema`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fdb%2Fschema.go#L471).

#### PDF Generation

The existing pattern for PDF generation can be found in the [`BillingHandler`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbilling.go#L31) in [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/api/handlers/billing.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbilling.go), specifically the [`GetInvoicePDF`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbilling.go#L456) function. This function uses the [`github.com/jung-kurt/gofpdf`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fgo.mod#L9) library (as seen in [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/go.mod`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fgo.mod)) to create and stream a PDF.

You can reuse this pattern by:

1.  Creating a new handler, e.g., `CertificateHandler`, similar to [`BillingHandler`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbilling.go#L31).
2.  Implementing a method like `GenerateCertificatePDF` within this handler.
3.  Fetching the `Certificate` data from your new collection.
4.  Using `gofpdf.New()` to create a new PDF document.
5.  Populating the PDF with certificate-specific details (learner name, course name, issue date, verification URL) using [`pdf.SetFont`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbilling.go#L485), [`pdf.Cell`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbilling.go#L486), [`pdf.Ln`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbilling.go#L487), etc.
6.  Setting [`Content-Type`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2FREADME.md#L273) to [`application/pdf`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fdocs.go#L346) and [`Content-Disposition`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fauth.go#L2380) in the HTTP response headers to allow download, similar to the [`GetInvoicePDF`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbilling.go#L456) function.

#### Unique Verification URL & Asset Serving

For a unique verification URL and serving, you can adapt the existing [`BrandingHandler`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbranding.go#L26) in [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/api/handlers/branding.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbranding.go).

1.  **Unique Verification URL:** The `VerificationCode` in your `Certificate` model would serve as the unique identifier. You would define a public API endpoint in your `CertificateHandler`, e.g., `/api/certificates/{verificationCode}`, which would fetch the certificate based on the `verificationCode`.
2.  **Asset Serving:** The [`ServeMedia`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbranding.go#L133) function in [`BrandingHandler`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbranding.go#L26) at [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/api/handlers/branding.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbranding.go) provides a pattern for serving binary data ([`BrandingAsset`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fbranding.go#L69)). You could:
    *   Store the generated PDF [`[]byte`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fcmd%2Fserver%2Fmain.go#L79) directly in your `Certificate` model (if sizes are manageable) or as a separate `CertificateAsset` model.
    *   Implement a function in `CertificateHandler` similar to [`ServeMedia`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fbranding.go#L133) that retrieves the PDF data based on the `VerificationCode` or `CertificateID` and streams it.
    *   Ensure proper [`Content-Type`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2FREADME.md#L273) and [`Cache-Control`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fcmd%2Fserver%2Fmain.go#L64) headers are set.

### 2. Drip Content

#### DripConfig Modeling

You would likely model `DripConfig` either as part of your `Course` or [`Section`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Ffrontend%2Fsrc%2Fpages%2Fadmin%2FBrandingPage.tsx#L638) model. Assuming a `Course` has [`Sections`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fapi%2Fhandlers%2Fdocs.go#L1016) and `Lessons`, you could add fields to these models:

*   **On `models.Course` or `models.Section`**:
    *   `DripEnabled`: [`bool`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fcmd%2Fserver%2Fmain.go#L364) to enable/disable drip for the course/section.
    *   `DripType`: [`string`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2FREADME.md#L349) (e.g., "time_since_enrollment", "sequential").
    *   `DripOffsetDays`: [`int`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fauth%2Fjwt.go#L37) (e.g., 7 days after enrollment for "time_since_enrollment").
    *   `PrerequisiteLessonID`: [`primitive.ObjectID`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go#L38) if content is released sequentially after another lesson.

#### Middleware/Handler Logic for Drip Eligibility

The system already utilizes middleware for various access control mechanisms, such as [`RequireAuth`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Fauth.go#L40), [`RequireTenant`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go#L28), [`RequireRole`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Frbac.go#L9), [`RequireActiveBilling`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go#L92), and [`RequireEntitlement`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go#L120) (see [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/middleware`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware)). You can create a new middleware for drip content:

1.  **New Drip Middleware**: Create a `RequireDripEligibility` middleware in [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/middleware`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware). This middleware would be applied to API endpoints that serve lesson content.

    ```go
    package middleware

    import (
    	"context"
    	"net/http"
    	"time"

    	"lastsaas/internal/db"
    	"lastsaas/internal/models"

    	"go.mongodb.org/mongo-driver/bson"
    	"go.mongodb.org/mongo-driver/bson/primitive"
    )

    // contextKey is a custom type for context keys to avoid collisions.
    type contextKey string

    const (
    	EnrollmentContextKey contextKey = "enrollment" // Assuming you'll have an enrollment model
    )

    type DripMiddleware struct {
    	db *db.MongoDB
    }

    func NewDripMiddleware(database *db.MongoDB) *DripMiddleware {
    	return &DripMiddleware{db: database}
    }

    func (m *DripMiddleware) RequireDripEligibility(next http.Handler) http.Handler {
    	return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    		tenant, ok := GetTenantFromContext(r.Context())
    		if !ok {
    			http.Error(w, `{"error":"Tenant context required"}`, http.StatusBadRequest)
    			return
    		}
    		user, ok := GetUserFromContext(r.Context())
    		if !ok {
    			http.Error(w, `{"error":"User context required"}`, http.StatusUnauthorized)
    			return
    		}

    		// Assume LessonID is extracted from the URL path (e.g., via mux.Vars)
    		// For this example, let's hardcode a lesson ID for demonstration
    		lessonIDStr := r.URL.Query().Get("lessonId") // Or from mux.Vars(r)["lessonId"]
    		if lessonIDStr == "" {
    			http.Error(w, `{"error":"Lesson ID required"}`, http.StatusBadRequest)
    			return
    		}
    		lessonID, err := primitive.ObjectIDFromHex(lessonIDStr)
    		if err != nil {
    			http.Error(w, `{"error":"Invalid lesson ID"}`, http.StatusBadRequest)
    			return
    		}

    		// 1. Fetch the lesson and its associated section/course for drip configuration
    		var lesson models.Lesson // You would define this model
    		// This would involve looking up the lesson, then its section, then its course
    		// For simplicity, let's assume lesson has a DripOffsetDays and a SectionID
    		err = m.db.Collection("lessons").FindOne(r.Context(), bson.M{"_id": lessonID}).Decode(&lesson)
    		if err != nil {
    			http.Error(w, `{"error":"Lesson not found"}`, http.StatusNotFound)
    			return
    		}

    		var section models.Section // You would define this model
    		err = m.db.Collection("sections").FindOne(r.Context(), bson.M{"_id": lesson.SectionID}).Decode(&section)
    		if err != nil {
    			http.Error(w, `{"error":"Section not found"}`, http.StatusNotFound)
    			return
    		}

    		// Check if drip content is enabled for this section
    		if !section.DripEnabled { // Assuming Section has DripEnabled field
    			next.ServeHTTP(w, r) // No drip, allow access
    			return
    		}

    		// 2. Fetch the user's enrollment record for the course
    		// This assumes an 'Enrollment' model that tracks when a user enrolled in a course.
    		var enrollment models.Enrollment // You would define this model
    		err = m.db.Collection("enrollments").FindOne(r.Context(), bson.M{
    			"userId":   user.ID,
    			"courseId": section.CourseID, // Assuming Section links to Course
    		}).Decode(&enrollment)

    		if err != nil {
    			http.Error(w, `{"error":"User not enrolled in course"}`, http.StatusForbidden)
    			return
    		}

    		// 3. Calculate eligibility based on time since enrollment
    		if section.DripType == "time_since_enrollment" {
    			requiredAccessDate := enrollment.EnrollmentDate.Add(time.Duration(section.DripOffsetDays) * 24 * time.Hour)
    			if time.Now().Before(requiredAccessDate) {
    				http.Error(w, `{"error":"Lesson not yet available. It will unlock on `+requiredAccessDate.Format("Jan 2, 2006")+`"}`, http.StatusPaymentRequired) // Or StatusForbidden
    				return
    			}
    		} else if section.DripType == "sequential" {
    			// For sequential drip, you would need to check if the prerequisite lesson
    			// has been completed. This would require a "LessonCompletion" model.
    			// For example:
    			// if lesson.PrerequisiteLessonID != nil {
    			//   var prerequisiteCompletion models.LessonCompletion
    			//   err := m.db.Collection("lesson_completions").FindOne(r.Context(), bson.M{
    			//     "userId": user.ID,
    			//     "lessonId": *lesson.PrerequisiteLessonID,
    			//     "completed": true,
    			//   }).Decode(&prerequisiteCompletion)
    			//   if err != nil { // Not found or not completed
    			//     http.Error(w, `{"error":"Complete previous lesson first"}`, http.StatusForbidden)
    			//     return
    			//   }
    			// }
    		}

    		// If eligible, proceed
    		next.ServeHTTP(w, r)
    	})
    }
    ```

2.  **Integration**: Apply this `RequireDripEligibility` middleware to the relevant API routes that serve lesson content. You would define these routes in the backend's main server file, [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/cmd/server/main.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fcmd%2Fserver%2Fmain.go), similar to how other middleware like [`RequireAuth`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Fauth.go#L40) and [`RequireTenant`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go#L28) are applied (see [API Routing and Endpoint Definition](#api-routing-and-endpoint-definition)).

#### Relevant Existing Patterns

*   **Usage Gating/Entitlement Checks**: The [`RequireEntitlement`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go#L120) middleware in [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/middleware/tenant.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go) provides a strong precedent. It checks [`plan.Entitlements`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go#L146) (defined in [`models.Plan`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fplanstore%2Fseed.go#L22) at [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/models/plan.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmodels%2Fplan.go)) to see if a tenant's plan grants access to a specific feature. Your drip middleware would operate similarly, but instead of checking a [`plan.Entitlements`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go#L146) map, it would check the `section.DripOffsetDays` against the `enrollment.EnrollmentDate`.
*   **Tenant/User Context**: The existing middleware architecture (e.g., [`GetUserFromContext`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Fauth.go#L174), [`GetTenantFromContext`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go#L79) in [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/middleware/auth.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Fauth.go) and [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/middleware/tenant.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go)) already provides the necessary user and tenant information that your drip middleware would need to retrieve enrollment records.
*   **Billing Status Checks**: [`RequireActiveBilling`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go#L92) in [`/jonradoff/lastsaas/backend/internal/middleware/tenant.go`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Finternal%2Fmiddleware%2Ftenant.go) prevents access based on the [`tenant.BillingStatus`](%2Fjonradoff%2Flastsaas%2Fbackend%2Fcmd%2Flastsaas%2Fcmd_tenants.go#L220). Your drip middleware would similarly block access if the conditions (e.g., `time.Now().Before(requiredAccessDate)`) are not met.
